1.title: Amore Motore
1.plot: Mickey attempts to help his scooter woo the heart of a mystery rider's scooter.

2.title: A Pete Scorned
2.plot: Pete enters into a deep depression when he fears that Mickey dislikes another rival more than him.

3.title: House Painters
3.plot: While Minnie is away, Mickey enlists the help of Donald and Goofy to repaint her house as a big surprise.

4.title: Surprise!
4.plot: Mickey's wish for a surprise-free birthday ends up becoming the biggest surprise of his life.

5.title: Hats Enough
5.plot: When the gang exclaims that they wouldn't be who they were without their hats, Mickey realizes that he doesn't have one and goes on the hunt for just the right one.

6.title: Safari, So Good
6.plot: When Mickey and Minnie miss the safari tour bus, they decide to take the walking scenic trip back to Arusha.

7.title: For Whom the Booth Tolls
7.plot: Mickey finds himself without a quarter for the tollbooth and decides to make a run for it.

8.title: Outta Time
8.plot:

1.title: Croissant de Triomphe
1.plot: When Minnie's cafe runs out of croissants, Mickey must deliver them to her fast, fighting wild traffic and other obstacles across Paris.

2.title: No Service
2.plot: Mickey and Donald try to buy lunch from a beachside snack shack but are unceremoniously turned down because of the classic "No shirt, no shoes, no service" admonition.

3.title: Yodelberg
3.plot: Mickey longs to visit Minnie atop her mountaintop chalet but quickly realizes that the threat of an avalanche has made the trek up the mountain more challenging than usual.

4.title: New York Weenie
4.plot: Mickey buys Minnie a hot dog, but it leads him on a merry chase through New York's Central Park.

5.title: Tokyo Go
5.plot: Mickey braves Tokyo's crazy commuting crowds aboard the bullet train as he tries to get to work on time.

6.title: Stayin' Cool
6.plot: On the hottest day of the year, Mickey, Donald and Goofy try to find ways to keep cool.

7.title: Gasp!
7.plot: After a sneaky cat breaks a fishbowl, Mickey attempts to save his pet fish.

8.title: Panda-monium
8.plot: At a zoo in Beijing, Mickey tries to take a picture of a cute little panda, but it proves to be quite camera-shy.

9.title: Bad Ear Day
9.plot: While Mickey prepares for a date with Minnie, he loses his trademark ears and must hunt them down.

10.title: Ghoul Friend
10.plot: Mickey's car breaks down near a graveyard, where he encounters a zombie that resembles Goofy.

11.title: Dog Show
11.plot: Mickey enters Pluto in a dog show, but when Pluto gets injured, Goofy is forced to step in as a substitute.

12.title: 'O Sole Minnie
12.plot: Mickey is an Italian gondolier trying to woo Minnie.

13.title: Potatoland
13.plot: Mickey and Donald build for Goofy a theme park out of potatoes.

14.title: Sleepwalkin'
14.plot: Mickey agrees to watch over Goofy after he reveals he has sleepwalking problems.

15.title: Flipperboobootosis
15.plot: Donald gets a foot ailment called "Flipperboobootosis", which Mickey and Goofy try to cure themselves when Donald won't go to the doctor.

16.title: Tapped Out
16.plot: Goofy volunteers Mickey to fight Pete in a wrestling match.

17.title: Third Wheel
17.plot: Goofy invites himself on Mickey's date with Minnie.

18.title: The Adorable Couple
18.plot: Mickey and Minnie attempt to make Donald and Daisy happy by showing them what life is all about.

1.title: Cable Car Chaos
1.plot: A cable car in San Francisco careens out of control, and it's up to Mickey and Minnie to stop it.

2.title: Fire Escape
2.plot: Minnie's apartment building is burning and Mickey attempts to save her. But first, he must also tend to every single one of the building's other tenants as well.

3.title: Eau du Minnie
3.plot: Minnie puts some new perfume in preparation for a date with Mickey, but it enchants the whole city.

4.title: O Futebol Classico
4.plot: Mickey fights for a seat at O Futebol Classico.

5.title: Down the Hatch
5.plot: Mickey, Donald and Goofy visit a science museum, but Mickey and Goofy are shrunk down to molecule size by a shrink ray and then are accidentally swallowed by Donald.

6.title: Goofy's Grandma
6.plot: Goofy's grandmother visits Mickey, but there's more to this sweet old lady than meets the eye.

7.title: Captain Donald
7.plot: Mickey is eager to ride on Donald's sailboat, but Donald reveals a shocking secret: he doesn't know how to sail.

8.title: Mumbai Madness
8.plot: What is supposed to be a routine trip for Mumbai rickshaw driver Mickey Mouse driving a jolly elephant passenger to a mountain turns out to be the journey of a lifetime with a very special guest.

9.title: The Boiler Room
9.plot: Mickey must rid the apartment basement of a monster.

10.title: Space Walkies
10.plot: Mickey and Pluto engage in a routine space mission, but then, at the least opportune moment, Pluto needs to go to the bathroom.

11.title: Mickey Monkey
11.plot: When a monkey swipes Mickey's clothes before he is to give his friends a cruise through the jungle, the gang mistakes the monkey for Mickey and vice-versa.

12.title: Clogged
12.plot: Minnie tries to get a windmill running to save a flower in her garden.

13.title: Goofy's First Love
13.plot: Goofy has fallen in love, so it's up to Mickey and Donald to help him be presentable.

14.title: Doggone Biscuits
14.plot: Minnie inadvertently feeds Pluto so many dog treats that he becomes overweight.

15.title: Workin' Stiff
15.plot: Mickey and Donald struggle to help Goofy at a job interview.

16.title: Al Rojo Vivo
16.plot: Mickey's red-hot temper entices a bull to chase him down the streets of Pamplona, Spain.

17.title: Bottle Shocked
17.plot: Mickey goes to buy a bottle of lemonade during the Grand Prix and must keep it safe as he takes it to Minnie.

18.title: A Flower for Minnie
18.plot: Mickey tries to find the perfect flower for Minnie, which proves to be no easy task.

19.title: Bronco Busted
19.plot: Mickey enters a rodeo contest to bail his friends out of a bad situation.

1.title: Coned
1.plot: When Pluto is forced to wear a dog cone, Mickey tries to make him feel better by wearing one himself. But it does not go well for him.

2.title: One Man Band
2.plot: Mickey travels through London searching for the perfect playing spot for his one-man band.

3.title: Wish Upon a Coin
3.plot: Mickey and Minnie visit the wishing well and wish for eternal happiness. However, the villainous Pete has other ideas and makes his move to steal all the wishes.

4.title: Movie Time
4.plot: Although the storm of the century is approaching, Mickey is still excited about his movie night. However, when he realizes he has no movies snacks, he must brave the elements to get them.

5.title: Shifting Gears
5.plot: Mickey is excited and ready for a great day at the beach. Unfortunately his car is not and a hilarious battle between the two ensues.

6.title: Black and White
6.plot: Mickey struggles with his fear of scary movies, but concedes to go to one with Minnie. However, when he gets to the theater and the movie starts, the real battle begins.

7.title: Feliz Cumpleanos!
7.plot: In this Spanish themed episode, Mickey celebrates his birthday while Minnie and Daisy perform a duet and Donald's mariachi band plays. However, chaos ensues when a rowdy group of piñatas crash his party.

8.title: Wonders of the Deep
8.plot: A submarine voyage to the bottom of the ocean turns dangerous when Mickey, Donald, and Goofy have to rescue Professor Von Drake from a giant sea creature.

9.title: Road Hogs
9.plot: After spending the day riding, Mickey and Minnie stop off at a local bar for a drink. Little do they know it's a hog biker bar and they aren't impressed by Mickey's ride.

10.title: No
10.plot: Mickey Mouse finds himself incapable of telling anyone no when they want to borrow anything. After it becomes a real problem, he turns to Donald for help.

11.title: Roughin' It
11.plot: The guys head out together on a camping trip. However, Donald and Goofy's idea of roughing it is very different than Mickey's.

12.title: Dancevidaniya
12.plot: When Mickey and Minnie head to the Russian ballet they find themselves in the middle of the performance.

13.title: Couple's Sweaters
13.plot: Mickey's itchy couple's sweater prevents him from enjoying his date with Minnie.

14.title: Turkish Delights
14.plot: When Mickey's new desert is a big hit at the local bazaar, the other merchants don't take kindly to him and attempt to eliminate his new found business.

15.title: Sock Burglar
15.plot: When a thief begins stealing every sock in town, Minnie makes it her personal mission to apprehend the criminal behind it.

16.title: Ku'u Lei Melody
16.plot: While spending a day on the Hawaiian beach with Donald and Goofy, Mickey struggles to compose his perfect melody and finds help from an island spirit.

17.title: Entombed
17.plot: Mickey leads Minnie on a treasure hunt in the Valley of the Tombs, but when the two are separated the adventure might prove too stressful for Mickey.

18.title: No Reservations
18.plot: Minnie, Daisy, and Clarabelle are excited about attending an exclusive restaurant for lunch, but the maitre d' has no record of their reservations.

19.title: Split Decisions
19.plot: Mickey leads Donald to Professor Von Drake's machine in another effort to cure his temper, with chaotic results.

20.title: Good Sports
20.plot: Mickey explains to two dirty playing basketball teams the importance of good sportsmanship as he takes a look in flashbacks of the good qualities that have been displayed in many sports since they first began.

21.title: Duck the Halls: A Mickey Mouse Christmas Special
21.plot: It's touch-and-go for Donald when, instead of heading south for the winter with Daisy and all the other ducks, he insists on staying with Mickey and the gang to enjoy all that Christmas has to offer.

1.title: Swimmin' Hole
1.plot: As summer begins, Mickey, Donald, and Goofy head out to enjoy the swimming hole only to find themselves in a battle with Pete over possession of it.

2.title: Canned
2.plot: On trash day, Mickey offers to take out his neighbor's garbage and finds himself doing a job that is more than he bargained for.

3.title: Touchdown and Out
3.plot: While enjoying a picnic and throwing the football around, Mickey, Donald, and Goofy are challenged to a very physical game of football by Pete and his gang.

4.title: Locked in Love
4.plot: After accidentally handcuffing his and Minnie's hands together in a heart-shaped lock, Mickey drops the key and the two frantically chase it together.

5.title: Bee Inspired
5.plot: Mickey attempts to provide inspiration for Minnie's painting only to be interrupted by a persistent bee.

6.title: Shipped Out
6.plot: Thinking that their cruise is the perfect place to relax, Mickey and Minnie suddenly find themselves forced to do all the activities the ship has to offer.

7.title: Three-Legged Race
7.plot: Minnie chooses to run the three-legged race with Daisy which forces Mickey to join Pete's team. Along the way Mickey struggles with the fact that everyone in the race is cheating to try and win.

8.title: Nature's Wonderland
8.plot: While touring the theme park "Nature's Wonderland", Mickey and Minnie get lost trying to find the "Rainbow Caverns" which leads to an adventure that's not on the map.

9.title: The Scariest Story Ever: A Mickey Mouse Halloween Spooktacular!
9.plot: At the end of Halloween night, Mickey attempts to cap off the evening by telling his and Donald's nephews the scariest story ever.

10.title: The Birthday Song
10.plot: Minnie composes a special song for Mickey's birthday, but before she can perform it for him, the notes leave the page and she has to round them up.

11.title: The Perfect Dream
11.plot: Mickey Mouse is awoken during his perfect dream and spends the rest of the night trying to get back to it.

12.title: Feed the Birds
12.plot: While feeding the birds the largest group prevent the smallest one from eating and Mickey has a hard time helping him get his fair share.

13.title: Carnaval
13.plot: While dancing in her feathered costume at a carnival in Rio, Minnie begins to fly and it's up to Mickey to help rescue her.

14.title: Year of the Dog
14.plot: Mickey's Lunar New Year feast is placed in jeopardy after a mysterious creature steals the main course.

15.title: The Fancy Gentleman
15.plot: After watching a romantic movie, Minnie decides to hire an instructor to teach Mickey how to be a fancy gentleman, but the results are not all that she hoped for.

16.title: New Shoes
16.plot: After wondering what it would be like to walk in each other's shoes, an unfortunate accident allows Mickey, Donald, and Goofy to do just that.

17.title: Springtime
17.plot: In this musical ballet short, a legendary battle is fought by Mickey, who attempts to bring spring, and Pete, who fights to continue winter.

18.title: Dumb Luck
18.plot: Mickey breaks a mirror which begins a terrible streak of bad luck and leads to his frantic search for a good luck charm.

19.title: Flushed!
19.plot: Thinking his sleeping pet goldfish has died, Mickey flushes it down the toilet which leads to a dangerous rescue.

20.title: Roll 'em
20.plot: A canister of film escapes during the shooting of movie which leads Mickey and Minnie on a wild rescue chase to recover it.

imdb.plot outline: Produced in 2D animation, the design esthetic for the Mickey Mouse cartoon shorts reaches back almost 80 years and borrows reverentially from the bold style of his 1930s design, but not before adding a few contemporary touches. Designs for other characters have a similar approach, favoring a "rubber-hose" cartoon style for more exaggerated animation. Background designs closely reflect the graphic design sense of 1950s and 1960s Disney cartoons. And for those true eagle-eyed Disney fans, the production team has also included the occasional homage to other icons from the storied Disney heritage.
